{
  "text": "Extant research on OCB focuses mainly on the affiliative dimensions of the construct [CITATION_1] . In spite of their potential as drivers of organizational change, the challenging dimensions of OCB receive little attention by researchers in works published to date [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . In this regard, and noting that few authors establish some of the possible antecedents of changeoriented OCB (e.g. [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] , this research aims at examining proactive behaviors in the field of organizational citizenship behavior. More specifically, this research is one of the first attempts to propose and test a model centered on transformational leadership and organizational climate as mediated antecedents of change-oriented organizational citizenship behavior, through their direct impact upon individuals' cognitive-emotional states. This model draws upon [CITATION_7] model of proactive motivation and the extant research that recognizes the importance of transformational leadership and innovative organizational climate upon this type of behavior (e.g., [CITATION_8] [CITATION_9] [CITATION_10] [CITATION_11] .",
